WEBVTT

00:00.201 --> 00:01.700
Sic ]

00:01.769 --> 00:03.168
[truck horn]

00:03.170 --> 00:04.903
<i> - Adult mark (vo):</i>
<i> I grew up</i>

00:04.939 --> 00:06.572
<i> In the middle</i>
<i> of nowhere.</i>

00:06.907 --> 00:08.540
[truck horn blares]

00:11.311 --> 00:14.246
<i> Of all the terrible days</i>
<i> of my lonely childhood</i>

00:14.315 --> 00:17.316
<i> The first day of junior high</i>
<i> was the worst.</i>

00:17.584 --> 00:19.718
<i> I didn't know</i>
<i> how to be a kid</i>

00:19.787 --> 00:21.887
<i> Because I was never</i>
<i> around any.</i>

00:22.223 --> 00:24.256
<i> No other kids</i>
<i> lived on my street.</i>

00:24.325 --> 00:26.692
<i> I had to attend the nearest</i>
<i> catholic junior high</i>

00:26.827 --> 00:29.060
<i> And that meant being bused</i>
<i> halfway across town</i>

00:29.096 --> 00:30.729
<i> With total strangers.</i>

00:31.665 --> 00:32.865
- Mark:
Ah!

00:33.000 --> 00:35.734
<i> - I shared a room with my</i>
<i> 80-year-old grandfather.</i>

00:35.869 --> 00:37.069
[sigh]

00:37.138 --> 00:38.604
- Good morning, pop.

00:38.739 --> 00:40.339
- Good mornin'.

00:42.609 --> 00:44.877
<i> - Pop washed himself</i>
<i> like a cat.</i>

00:45.479 --> 00:47.146
<i> Nothing gets you</i>
<i> out of bed faster</i>

00:47.148 --> 00:49.748
<i> Than being mooned</i>
<i> by an octogenarian.</i>

00:49.750 --> 00:51.083
[phone ringing]

00:51.085 --> 00:52.484
[fiddle music]

00:52.486 --> 00:54.619
- Mary:
Oh, I'm good girl, yes.

00:54.621 --> 00:57.055
My god, heard all about
your husband.

00:57.091 --> 00:58.490
Oh, don't be talking.

00:58.492 --> 01:00.492
Shocking, isn't it,
him full up with the cancer?

01:00.528 --> 01:03.228
<i> - My father worked</i>
<i> at the radio station next door,</i>

01:03.230 --> 01:05.530
<i> But my mother</i>
<i> was a radio station.</i>

01:05.599 --> 01:07.799
<i> She shot out gossip</i>
<i> like a machine gun.</i>

01:07.835 --> 01:10.635
- Yes, I'm sure the crowd
at the hospital knows best,

01:10.704 --> 01:12.838
But I did hear
that dr. Hall left his wife

01:12.907 --> 01:15.507
For a gallbladder patient
and he started drinking again.

01:15.642 --> 01:17.142
- Kettle's boiled there, mary.

01:17.211 --> 01:19.111
- Would somebody
get that bloody kettle?

01:19.180 --> 01:20.579
I'm comforting alice.

01:20.714 --> 01:22.247
Her husband's
good as dead.

01:22.249 --> 01:24.716
<i> - Nothing said,</i>
<i> "I'm too sick to go to school"</i>

01:24.718 --> 01:26.852
<i> Like a temperature</i>
<i> of a 100 degrees.</i>

01:26.854 --> 01:28.686
- Oh, yes, girl, at least
the alcohol would kill

01:28.722 --> 01:30.022
Whatever germs
he's apt for getting

01:30.157 --> 01:31.523
From that
gall-less hussey.

01:31.525 --> 01:32.957
- Mom,

01:32.993 --> 01:34.426
I can't believe this.

01:34.495 --> 01:36.161
First day of school,

01:36.296 --> 01:37.463
I'm sick.

01:37.598 --> 01:38.930
- Mike jr.:
He's faking!

01:38.999 --> 01:40.599
He had his head
over the kettle!

01:40.668 --> 01:41.834
- See?

01:41.969 --> 01:43.401
This type of scrutiny

01:43.471 --> 01:45.337
Is exactly why I don't share
how I'm feeling with you people.

01:45.406 --> 01:48.173
- Sweet jesus.
Tony walsh died.

01:48.675 --> 01:50.442
Some sort of prick
he was.

01:50.577 --> 01:53.278
Still, can't wait
for that wake.

01:53.547 --> 01:55.881
Hey, mark, if you're
home sick, come with me -

01:55.950 --> 01:57.482
Spread a few germs
around.

01:57.485 --> 02:00.519
See if you can't take down
a few more of the bastards.

02:01.088 --> 02:02.621
- Which funeral home?

02:02.690 --> 02:04.022
- Carmel's.

02:04.091 --> 02:05.524
- Ah. Better sandwiches
at caul's.

02:05.659 --> 02:07.759
- Hey, how come he gets to
stay at home and go to awake?

02:07.895 --> 02:09.494
- He's faking sick.
- Hold on, dear.

02:09.497 --> 02:11.563
Nobody is going
to a wake.

02:12.433 --> 02:13.765
Now, mark, honey,

02:13.801 --> 02:16.234
I know you're nervous
about going to school.

02:16.270 --> 02:18.770
I know you're worried
about getting picked on

02:18.772 --> 02:20.505
And beaten up
and made fun of...

02:20.574 --> 02:23.375
- Wow, you really know
how to cheer a guy up.

02:23.444 --> 02:24.643
- But you
don't need to be.

02:24.712 --> 02:26.111
I mean, sure those things
will happen,

02:26.180 --> 02:28.447
But it's how you respond
that matters.

02:28.449 --> 02:30.015
You just
be yourself.

02:30.150 --> 02:32.184
- Jeez, don't do that.

02:32.253 --> 02:34.519
- Yes, don't do
anything harsh, now.

02:34.555 --> 02:37.856
- People can tell when you're
trying to be some'n you're not.

02:37.858 --> 02:39.857
Now, everyone might think
you're strange,

02:39.894 --> 02:42.260
But you
are the sweetest boy I know.

02:42.396 --> 02:43.728
- Strange?

02:43.797 --> 02:45.597
- Nervous or not, if you don't
get on that bloody bus,

02:45.633 --> 02:48.000
I'm going to pick you up
like a bloody baby

02:48.135 --> 02:49.534
And carry you onto it

02:49.570 --> 02:51.002
And then they're going to
make fun of you even worse

02:51.038 --> 02:52.771
Than they
already will.

02:52.906 --> 02:54.539
- Great pep talk.

02:54.875 --> 02:56.341
- Yes, yes...

02:56.743 --> 02:58.877
- Heya, turn that up,
your father's on.

02:58.946 --> 03:00.212
<i> - Dick:</i>
<i> We go now live</i>

03:00.347 --> 03:02.414
<i> To the scene</i>
<i> of a traffic accident</i>

03:02.483 --> 03:04.816
Of ungodly proportions.

03:05.219 --> 03:08.219
Here's mike critch
with the vocm news.

03:08.255 --> 03:10.822
<i> - The old man had a way</i>
<i> of spinning small town news</i>

03:10.958 --> 03:13.691
<i> That made the mundane</i>
<i> seem earth-shattering.</i>

03:13.727 --> 03:15.026
- Mike sr.:
Two moose were struck

03:15.062 --> 03:16.562
On the
trans-canada highway.

03:16.697 --> 03:17.996
The sex of the moose...

03:18.131 --> 03:19.498
Has not yet
been released

03:19.500 --> 03:21.700
But early reports indicate
that two amorous moose

03:21.702 --> 03:23.769
Were locked in combat
in a show of strength

03:23.904 --> 03:26.305
In the outbound lane
when a third moose,

03:26.440 --> 03:27.973
The object
of their affection,

03:28.042 --> 03:29.875
Looked on unamused.

03:30.411 --> 03:31.977
Two men killed...

03:32.112 --> 03:33.578
One seriously.

03:33.581 --> 03:37.982
Mike critch, first on the scene
for the vocm news service.

03:38.018 --> 03:39.818
[ambulance siren whoops]

03:40.354 --> 03:42.721
You know what hospital
they went to?

03:42.923 --> 03:44.122
Was it st. Claire's?

03:44.158 --> 03:45.457
Health sciences?

03:45.459 --> 03:47.459
<i> - I envied</i>
<i> that dead moose.</i>

03:47.461 --> 03:48.860
<i> Its suffering was over</i>

03:48.862 --> 03:50.862
<i> And mine</i>
<i> was just beginning.</i>

03:55.102 --> 03:56.701
- Go! Carry on!

03:56.770 --> 03:57.935
I'm good.

03:57.972 --> 04:00.072
- Are you getting on?
- I'll catch the next one.

04:00.207 --> 04:02.007
- There's no next one.

04:02.142 --> 04:04.075
- Mark!
Hey, mark.

04:04.077 --> 04:05.710
Did you
see the moose?

04:05.746 --> 04:07.379
Mark!

04:09.316 --> 04:10.782
<i> - These were</i>
<i> big kids.</i>

04:10.818 --> 04:12.617
<i> Some had</i>
<i> wispy mustaches</i>

04:12.620 --> 04:15.020
<i> That reminded me</i>
<i> of the fuzz on kiwis.</i>

04:17.458 --> 04:19.524
<i> -</i> Keep an
eye on me.

04:22.562 --> 04:24.763
<i> - There was no</i>
<i> going back now.</i>

04:25.099 --> 04:26.364
<i> And, apparently,</i>

04:26.400 --> 04:28.467
<i> There was no</i>
<i> sitting down either.</i>

04:33.974 --> 04:35.240
<i> Wait a minute.</i>

04:35.309 --> 04:36.708
<i> Does that kid</i>
<i> have a kid?</i>

04:36.744 --> 04:39.244
- Young fox: What are you
looking at, prick?

04:39.379 --> 04:40.979
[laughter]

04:43.984 --> 04:45.617
[gentle music]

04:49.323 --> 04:50.889
- Hi.

04:52.526 --> 04:54.992
I can't tell you
how much I appreciate it.

04:55.029 --> 04:57.329
My name's mark,
st. Paul's elementary.

04:57.464 --> 04:59.031
Class of '86.

04:59.166 --> 05:00.665
Ow.

05:00.734 --> 05:02.967
- Fox: That's for making us come
all the way out here to get you.

05:03.003 --> 05:05.137
Who the hell was out there
on the highway?

05:05.139 --> 05:06.538
Was that
your dad?

05:06.540 --> 05:08.339
Why is he so old?

05:08.341 --> 05:10.609
- Him?
I don't know that guy.

05:13.147 --> 05:15.614
<i> - Dick: First day of school</i>
<i> in the capital city.</i>

05:15.749 --> 05:17.482
<i> Now, mike,</i>
<i> that was your boy</i>

05:17.551 --> 05:19.784
<i> Getting on that school bus</i>
<i> there, wasn't it?</i>

05:19.820 --> 05:21.252
<i> - Mike sr.:</i>
<i> Yes, dick, I'd like to send</i>

05:21.288 --> 05:22.587
A bouquet out
to my son, mark,

05:22.623 --> 05:24.889
On his first day
at st. Bridget's school.

05:24.925 --> 05:27.092
Mark, I know you're scared, son,
but I'm sure<i> you're making</i>

05:27.161 --> 05:29.728
<i> Lots of good friends</i>
<i> on the school bus.</i>

05:29.863 --> 05:31.229
[laughter]

05:31.298 --> 05:33.064
- Oh, yeah.

05:33.067 --> 05:34.499
Him, that-that's
my dad.

05:34.501 --> 05:36.468
[laughter]

05:36.970 --> 05:38.337
That's my lunch.

05:38.472 --> 05:39.905
We can share
if you want.

05:40.040 --> 05:42.006
<i> - Just when I thought</i>
<i> it couldn't get any worse...</i>

05:42.076 --> 05:44.509
- Tin of drink,
chips and a bun ...

05:44.511 --> 05:46.111
We're going to get along
just fine.

05:46.180 --> 05:47.512
<i> - I met her brothers.</i>

05:47.514 --> 05:49.514
- Silver fox:
Look at you, ah, poor thing.

05:49.516 --> 05:51.316
This is gonna suck.

05:51.585 --> 05:53.285
<i> - Older mark:</i>
<i> Bullying was her family busine.</i>

05:53.287 --> 05:55.887
<i> Each copper-headed thug</i>
<i> controlled a separate grade</i>

05:55.889 --> 05:58.256
<i> And they all shared</i>
<i> the same nickname.</i>

05:58.425 --> 05:59.758
<i> Fox.</i>

05:59.893 --> 06:02.794
- (singsong) ah-ha.
Fox got a boyfriend.

06:02.929 --> 06:04.796
- Shut up!
He's not my boyfriend.

06:04.798 --> 06:06.297
- Oh, she's getting mad.

06:06.367 --> 06:09.734
<i> - Fox was the only girl,</i>
<i> but when it came to bullying,</i>

06:09.737 --> 06:11.703
<i> She wanted to smash</i>
<i> the glass ceiling...</i>

06:11.838 --> 06:12.871
- Ow!

06:12.873 --> 06:14.372
<i> - And use my head</i>
<i> to break it.</i>

06:14.441 --> 06:16.174
- Fox! Fox! Fox!
Fox! Fox! Fox!

06:16.210 --> 06:19.411
<i> - Mike sr: Local authorities</i>
<i> have asked me to announce</i>

06:19.413 --> 06:22.481
<i> They're having a raffle on</i>
<i> 800 pounds of moose meat.</i>

06:22.616 --> 06:24.215
["tom sawyer"
by rush plays]

06:24.251 --> 06:26.084
[school bell]

06:26.086 --> 06:27.719
[excited chatter]

06:27.821 --> 06:29.488
<i> ♪ a modern-day</i>
<i> warrior ♪</i>

06:29.490 --> 06:30.889
<i> ♪ a mean, mean stride ♪</i>

06:30.958 --> 06:33.157
<i> ♪ today's tom sawyer,</i>
<i> mean, mean ride ♪</i>

06:33.159 --> 06:35.560
<i> - Vice principal (on pa):</i>
<i> Welcome back, students.</i>

06:35.695 --> 06:37.562
<i> Make your way to class</i>
<i> in an orderly fashion.</i>

06:37.598 --> 06:40.932
<i> And would tommy dunphy report</i>
<i> to the vice principal's office.</i>

06:41.067 --> 06:42.667
<i> ♪</i>

06:45.305 --> 06:47.906
<i> ♪ though his mind</i>
<i> is not for rent ♪</i>

06:47.908 --> 06:50.442
<i> ♪ don't put him down</i>
<i> as arrogant ♪</i>

06:50.844 --> 06:53.245
<i> ♪ his reserve,</i>
<i> a quiet defense ♪</i>

06:53.713 --> 06:55.981
<i> ♪ riding out</i>
<i> the day's events ♪</i>

06:57.718 --> 06:59.918
- Sister margaret:
Settle down, children.

06:59.920 --> 07:01.720
Quickly.

07:02.589 --> 07:03.922
Good morning,
class.

07:03.991 --> 07:06.591
We have some new students
joining us today.

07:06.593 --> 07:08.727
Mark and ritchie,
stand up.

07:09.496 --> 07:10.929
[chair scraping]

07:11.465 --> 07:14.766
<i> - Ritchie was filipino</i>
<i> and the only kid of colour</i>

07:14.835 --> 07:18.136
<i> In a school that had the sum</i>
<i> diversity of a snowbank.</i>

07:18.271 --> 07:19.670
[giggling]

07:19.706 --> 07:20.972
[silence]

07:21.008 --> 07:23.008
- Yes, well,
you may be seated.

07:23.143 --> 07:25.944
Our principal
would like to say a few words

07:26.079 --> 07:28.079
As we start
our new year.

07:28.081 --> 07:30.081
- Sister rose:
Thank you, sister margaret.

07:30.117 --> 07:32.684
Who wants to play
a guessing game?

07:32.886 --> 07:34.886
<i> - I smelled a trap.</i>

07:34.888 --> 07:37.889
- I'm going to pass this
envelope around the classroom.

07:37.891 --> 07:39.624
Feel the weight of it.

07:39.759 --> 07:40.958
The shape of it.

07:40.994 --> 07:43.228
Guess what's inside of it.

07:43.297 --> 07:44.563
- Is it a bible,
sister?

07:44.698 --> 07:46.398
<i> - Suck up.</i>

07:46.800 --> 07:48.533
- Is it a frisbee,
sister.

07:48.535 --> 07:50.368
<i> - Frisbees are round,</i>
<i> idiot.</i>

07:55.242 --> 07:56.875
- A dump truck.

07:58.045 --> 07:59.444
- This...

07:59.513 --> 08:01.146
Is...

08:02.516 --> 08:04.115
A strap.

08:04.117 --> 08:06.384
<i> - Corporal punishment</i>
<i> had been outlawed</i>

08:06.420 --> 08:07.786
<i> But nobody</i>
<i> told the nuns.</i>

08:07.788 --> 08:10.454
- Boys and girls
who are sent to the office

08:10.491 --> 08:11.923
Will receive three...

08:11.959 --> 08:14.392
Straps
to each hand.

08:14.428 --> 08:16.727
Then you could
come back here

08:16.763 --> 08:18.930
With your sore
red hands

08:18.966 --> 08:21.700
And think about
what you have done.

08:22.536 --> 08:24.135
Well,

08:24.137 --> 08:25.537
Enough fun.

08:25.772 --> 08:27.405
Sister margaret...

08:28.208 --> 08:29.874
They're all yours.

08:30.344 --> 08:31.610
- Thank you,
sister rose.

08:31.745 --> 08:33.611
Very informative

08:33.747 --> 08:35.614
- As always.
- [door slams shut]

08:35.616 --> 08:37.682
Children, take out your
geography books.

08:39.553 --> 08:41.186
♪

08:44.391 --> 08:47.659
- Silver fox:
Thanks for the chips, loser.

08:48.328 --> 08:49.760
See you on the bus!

08:49.796 --> 08:53.431
- Gary: What the hell
do you have on your feet?

08:53.700 --> 08:55.166
- They're orthopaedics.

08:55.168 --> 08:57.302
I didn't think
I needed orthopaedic shoes

08:57.371 --> 08:59.303
But I stand corrected.

08:59.973 --> 09:01.706
- Why aren't you
wearing sneakers?

09:01.708 --> 09:03.341
<i> - Just be yourself.</i>

09:03.377 --> 09:04.842
- I like a comfortable shoe.

09:04.912 --> 09:07.445
I'm not a runner;
I'm more of a stroller.

09:07.514 --> 09:09.914
I have asthma,
but I've always said

09:09.917 --> 09:12.083
Asthma doesn't
have me.

09:14.755 --> 09:18.056
Oh, what kind of music
are you guys listening to?

09:18.125 --> 09:19.524
- Van halen.

09:19.659 --> 09:22.193
- Oh, I hear
he is very good.

09:22.796 --> 09:24.996
- What kind of music
do you like?

09:25.032 --> 09:28.133
<i> - Ah, the dreaded, "what kind f</i>
<i> music do you like?" question.</i>

09:28.268 --> 09:30.802
- Well, I like
all kinds of music.

09:30.804 --> 09:32.003
Um...

09:32.072 --> 09:33.672
Dean martin
more than sinatra.

09:33.674 --> 09:35.941
Well, I like
early sinatra.

09:36.343 --> 09:37.876
Not the new stuff.

09:37.878 --> 09:39.711
[school bell]

09:42.382 --> 09:44.281
- Weirdo.
- Ow!

09:44.283 --> 09:45.516
[thud]

09:45.552 --> 09:47.018
♪

09:56.263 --> 09:58.229
<i> - I was not made</i>
<i> for gym class.</i>

09:58.298 --> 10:00.231
<i> I was an asthmatic</i>
<i> with fallen arches</i>

10:00.233 --> 10:01.900
<i> And no hand-eye</i>
<i> coordination.</i>

10:01.902 --> 10:04.302
<i> I had excellent foot-mouth</i>
<i> coordination, though.</i>

10:04.371 --> 10:06.170
[whistle]

10:06.239 --> 10:07.872
- I'm mr. Byrne.

10:09.843 --> 10:11.242
Today,

10:11.278 --> 10:13.445
We are going to use
this parachute

10:13.580 --> 10:15.847
To achieve
physical excellence

10:15.849 --> 10:17.515
As a team.

10:18.051 --> 10:19.984
Where are your
gym clothes?

10:20.020 --> 10:21.386
- I didn't bring 'em.

10:21.388 --> 10:22.721
It's first day.

10:22.856 --> 10:24.088
I-I didn't think that--

10:24.124 --> 10:26.724
- When it comes
to parachute-based sports,

10:26.793 --> 10:30.327
We are only as strong
as our weakest link.

10:30.497 --> 10:31.663
What's your name?

10:31.732 --> 10:33.999
- Mark.
- What's your name?

10:36.136 --> 10:37.802
- I-I-I think
he's ritchie.

10:37.871 --> 10:39.504
- We are
only as strong

10:39.639 --> 10:41.339
As mark and ritchie.

10:41.675 --> 10:43.675
- [blows whistle]
- parachute!

10:43.744 --> 10:45.143
I'm going to call out
two names

10:45.212 --> 10:47.612
And those kids
are going to switch places.

10:47.747 --> 10:49.748
<i> - Don't pick me and ritchie.</i>
<i> Don't pick me and ritchie.</i>

10:49.883 --> 10:50.948
- Mark and ritchie.

10:50.984 --> 10:52.817
- [blows whistle]
- parachute!

10:53.153 --> 10:54.552
<i> ♪</i>

10:56.289 --> 10:59.690
<i> - The more I tried to get out,</i>
<i> the more I panicked.</i>

10:59.726 --> 11:01.358
<i> And ritchie</i>
<i> was no help.</i>

11:01.395 --> 11:03.028
[groan]

11:11.638 --> 11:13.271
<i> [unenthusiastic</i>
<i> whistle]</i>

11:16.810 --> 11:18.309
<i> Like in prison,</i>

11:18.311 --> 11:21.979
<i> We got one hour a day</i>
<i> to eat outside in the yard.</i>

11:21.981 --> 11:23.648
- Silver fox:
Move it loser.

11:24.017 --> 11:25.883
<i> - No matter how badly</i>
<i> I had it,</i>

11:25.919 --> 11:27.686
